Please see CHANGELOG at master branch for latest stable version.

2016-07-19
 - 'AllowAssociativeArray' and 'Formatted' are now public properties.
 - AllowAssociativeArray replaces the old setter method.
 - Property 'Formatted' (default: true) indicates a formatted (whitespaces)
   XML after Serialization.
 - Added a method 'RebuildAssociative()' to transform the key-value pairs
   back to an associative array.
 - 'Serialize()' now can get the name of the root node.
 - 'Deserialize()' now keeps the name of the root node.
 - 'GetRootName()' returns the name of the root node from the last deserialization.

2015-11-24
 - Renamed method from 'AssociativeArray()' to 'AllowAssociativeArray()'.

2015-10-28
 - Added UnitTest.
 - Added Makefile for less work.
 - Associative arrays are errors by default.
 - Associative arrays (dictionaries) are difficult to parse.
 - Explicitly enable assoc. arrays with 'AssociativeArray(true)'.

2015-09-25
 - Initial release.
 - very basic functionality.
 - only 'Serialize()' and 'Deserialize()' available.
 - no properties/configuration possible.
